'''NSC'''

  1.) National Security Council-part of congress charged with overseeing the security of the United Statesand addressing issues of conflict; comprised of the President, Secretary of Defense, Secretary of State heads of the major Agencies: the CIA, NSA, FBI, DHS, FIMA and the Joint Choiefs of staff from the different armed Service branches.  It usually also includes special council (advisors)to the president. 2.)  Can also refer to Natick Soldier Center (US Army).